☁️ Practical 6: Deploy Web Application using S3 Bucket
🔧 Prerequisites

An AWS account (free tier works)
A simple web app (HTML/CSS/JS files)


STEP 1: Log in to AWS Console

Go to https://aws.amazon.com
Click Sign In to the Console
Enter your credentials and log in


STEP 2: Navigate to S3

In the search bar at the top, type S3
Click on S3 under Services


STEP 3: Create a New S3 Bucket

Click Create bucket
Fill in the details:

Bucket name: Give a unique name (e.g., my-webapp-12345) — must be globally unique
AWS Region: Choose your nearest region (e.g., ap-south-1 for Mumbai)


Under Block Public Access settings:

❗ Uncheck "Block all public access"
Confirm the warning checkbox that appears


Leave other settings as default
Click Create bucket


STEP 4: Upload Your Web Files

Click on your newly created bucket
Click Upload
Click Add files and select your web files:

index.html (main file)
CSS, JS, images, etc.


Click Upload


STEP 5: Enable Static Website Hosting

Go to the Properties tab of your bucket
Scroll down to Static website hosting
Click Edit
Select Enable
Set:

Index document: index.html
Error document: error.html (optional)


Click Save changes
📋 Copy the website endpoint URL shown at the bottom (you'll need it later)


STEP 6: Set Bucket Policy (Make Files Public)

Go to the Permissions tab of your bucket
Scroll to Bucket Policy and click Edit
Paste the following policy (replace YOUR-BUCKET-NAME with your actual bucket name):

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "PublicReadGetObject",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::sai-static-website-2026/*"
    }
  ]
}
Click Save changes


STEP 7: Access Your Deployed Web App

Go back to Properties → Static website hosting
Click on the Bucket website endpoint URL
🎉 Your web application is now live on the internet!


📝 Example Output
Your website will be accessible at a URL like:
http://my-webapp-12345.s3-website.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com
